Japan's Honda Motor Co. Ltd. said Friday its  consolidated pre-tax earnings tumbled 47 percent from a year earlier to 46.9  billion yen (455 million dollars) in the year to March.
The company said its worldwide sales dropped seven percent to 3,860  billion yen in the same period.
Honda forecast improved earnings of 52 billion for the current year with  sales recovering to around 4,000 billion yen.
